node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Mandy on July 25, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: A crisp, sunny winter’s morning here and the wind has gone! So thankful the girls had their moult and grew feathers back before the cold weather hit. There’s been so many years where they lost their feathers in the middle of winter! #Aussiechickens #herechookchook #cottagegarden #freerangechickens #poules #galline #höns  #hühner #galinhas #abcmyphoto

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Mandy on July 24, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: My sweet girl, Mary Ellen, laid her first egg yesterday after a long well earned break. She was very vocal about it beforehand too🙉! I can only imagine what it’s going to be like when the others start laying again, I’ve got used to the quiet! I haven’t had eggs here for months and that’s just how I like it. Chickens naturally have a break from producing eggs, all their energy goes into growing new feathers after their moult and coping with the cold weather. Eggs are seasonal and real treasures, an added bonus when you keep chickens. 🥚 #aussiechickens #herechookchook #cottagegarden #freerangechickens #poules #galline #höns  #hühner #galinhas #abcmyphoto #gardeningaustralia

node.text: We were going to present FLUFFY BUTTS IN FORMATION but Barbara Ann chickened out (see what I did there?😂). Elly May carried on the performance with a little cameo appearance by the frazzle boy at the end. Thank you for your attendance and applause 👏. #fluffybuttsinformation #fluffybuttfriday #aussiechickens #herechookchook #cottagegarden #freerangechickens #poules #galline #höns  #hühner #galinhas #abcmyphoto

node.text: I love how the morning light on the tree looks like fairy lights. Elly May is fluffed up against the cold this morning! #Aussiechickens #herechookchook #cottagegarden #freerangechickens #poules #galline #höns  #hühner #galinhas #abcmyphoto

node.text: You’d never think from this sunny pic that the temp early this morning was-0.5°C with a feels like temp of -4.3°C 🥶. The cold doesn’t seem to bother the chooks though, they just go about their foraging business as usual🤷🏻‍♀️. #Aussiechickens #herechookchook #cottagegarden #freerangechickens #poules #galline #höns  #hühner #galinhas #abcmyphoto

node.text: I thought I was capturing a sweet Mother and son moment, then she pecked him!😂 Pearl and the frazzle boy. #Aussiechickens #herechookchook #cottagegarden #freerangechickens #poules #galline #höns  #hühner #galinhas #abcmyphoto

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Mandy on July 15, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: It’s been raining on and off here today. The little frazzle boy’s feathers are unfrazzled! And btw, I still haven’t heard him crow, that’s why he’s still living here in town, where roosters are not allowed 🚫. He’s 9 1/2 months old now. It’s funny that Barbara Ann tried to crow the other day and he’s a boy, but still nothing!🤷🏻‍♀️. #Aussiechickens #herechookchook #cottagegarden #freerangechickens #poules #galline #höns  #hühner #galinhas #abcmyphoto

node.text: My chooks celebrating 4th July 🇺🇸. I’m really sad that  #australiapost has put an end to my hat business overseas. They increased the cost of posting my hats from $3.60 to over $20, making postage costs more than the price of a hat!! I am still selling them in Australia, but I have really lost my mojo, and problems with my hands doesn’t help!! I am trying to get back into stocking my Etsy shop so any Aussies interested in chicken hats, follow the link in my bio and put in your orders. New hat ideas welcome too! #herechookchookchickenhats #aussiechickens #herechookchook #cottagegarden #freerangechickens #poules #galline #höns  #hühner #galinhas #abcmyphoto
